Hello,

We are currently using your vanish plugin on our Minecraft server and have a question regarding the interaction between vanish and fly.

When a staff member enters vanish mode, they automatically gain access to /fly, which works as expected. However, our staff members already have fly permissions through their rank.

The issue we are running into is the following:
When a staff member exits vanish, the plugin also disables fly, even though the player still has permission to fly via their rank. This results in staff members unexpectedly losing fly mode after leaving vanish.

Is there a way to:

prevent the plugin from toggling /fly on vanish disable, or
disable the vanish–fly linkage entirely, so fly is not modified when entering or leaving vanish?
We would prefer that the plugin does not interfere with existing fly permissions, and only handles invisibility-related functionality.

If this is configurable (via config options or permissions), we would love to know how to set this up.
If not, is this something that could be considered for a future update?

Thanks in advance for your time and for maintaining the plugin.
